{
  "texts": [
    "FjORD [39] implements ordered dropout, a technique that organizes knowledge within a deep neural network in a structured and hierarchical manner.",
    "This allows for the extraction of compact sub-models without retraining.",
    "Ordered dropout enhances computational efficiency by dropping model components in sequence rather than at random, aligning with the optimization capabilities of contemporary linear algebra libraries.",
    "The approach is complemented by a self-distillation process to refine the model further.Building on these foundations, PruneFL [41] proposed a two-stage model pruning process specifically designed for FL environments.",
    "Initially, a \"warm-up\" phase involves selecting a single capable and trusted client to prune the model using its local data, thereby starting the FL process with a streamlined model."
  ]
}